						               													<description>Ever wanted to be Charles Bronson in &amp;quot;Death Wish,&amp;quot; just gunning down any punk that gets in your face, sasses you back, or even looks at you funny?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the box cover:&amp;#10;&amp;quot;You've read about this sort of thing in the newspapers and magazines. Now you can play it!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Starting with a handgun and six bullets, up to four players attempt to survive a harrowing ride from Brooklyn to the Bronx on a New York City subway system jam-packed with vicious Punks. Shoving matches, car derailments, nosy security guards, overworked policemen, and botched subway transfers add to the game's (and your) &amp;quot;Angst&amp;quot; level the closer you get to home. &amp;#10;Game mechanics are basic roll-and-move, with &amp;quot;Punk&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Make My Day!&amp;quot; cards being drawn if you land on the appropriate space. Game components are semi-professional&amp;#10;as regards the gameboard, rules, and cards, along with four metal &amp;quot;handgun&amp;quot; tokens and twenty four bullets. You will need every one of them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Interestingly, the rules include guidelines for a Roundtable Discussion to be held after the game is finished. &amp;#10;Just try to keep a straight face!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
